":"headwind","explanation":"Macro event clustering is increasing the probability of sharp cross-asset repricing."},{"signal":"Geopolitical severity","state":"High","score":-2,"impact":"headwind","explanation":"Geopolitical stress is elevated enough to cap aggression and require hedging discipline."}]},"marketSummary":{"indices":[{"name":"S&P 500","ticker":"SPX","level":5312,"changePct":0.7,"trend":"up"},{"name":"Nasdaq 100","ticker":"NDX","level":18642,"changePct":1.1,"trend":"up"},{"name":"MSCI EM","ticker":"EEM","level":43.8,"changePct":-0.3,"trend":"flat"},{"name":"Gold","ticker":"XAU","level":2184,"changePct":0.4,"trend":"up"}],"majorIndexTrend":"bullish","usdTrend":"down","bondYieldDirection":"flat","goldBehavior":"stable","oilBehavior":"stable","volatilityState":"calm","vix":15.8,"breadthPct":62,"macroEventFlags":{"inflationRisk":true,"centralBankRisk":true,"growthRisk":false,"liquidityRisk":false},"geopoliticalSeverity":"High"},"macroSummary":{"tone":"cautious","headline":"Disinflation is improving, but yields and policy communication still cap full aggression.","bullets":["inflation cooling","yields rising","growth weakening","policy uncertainty elevated"],"explanation":"Macro conditions still allow selective risk-taking, yet yields rising and policy uncertainty elevated keep the market from becoming a clean all-clear."},"geopoliticalBoard":{"asOf":"2026-03-14T09:00:00Z","summary":{"headline":"Shipping, conflict, and policy shocks keep the geopolitical overlay firmly active.","overlaySeverity":"High","overlayScore":76,"activeCount":7,"posture":"Geopolitical risk is elevated but still tradable with selectivity.","dominantChannels":["Commodities","Currencies","Risk sentiment","Inflation"],"actionBias":["reduce risk: Border conflict flare-up drives defense and haven demand","add hedge: Red Sea shipping corridor remains under intermittent threat","monitor: US-China semiconductor restrictions broaden"]},"events":[{"id":"geo-7","title":"Border conflict flare-up drives defense and haven demand","category":"war/conflict","region":"Eastern Europe","severity":"Critical","severityScore":90,"status":"Escalating","affectedRegions":["Eastern Europe","Europe","Global"],"transmissionChannels":[{"channel":"commodities","direction":"higher","intensity":3,"explanation":"Conflict risk lifts energy, grain, and industrial input premia across Europe."},{"channel":"currencies","direction":"mixed","intensity":2,"explanation":"European FX and safe-haven flows respond quickly when military risk escalates."},{"channel":"riskSentiment","direction":"lower","intensity":4,"explanation":"Conflict headlines compress risk appetite and increase the value of defensive hedges."}],"beneficiaries":["Defense","Gold","USD cash","Energy"],"losers":["European cyclicals","Travel","Discretionary"],"actionSuggestion":"reduce risk","chips":["conflict risk","safe havens","Europe exposure"],"implication":"Pushes safe-haven demand higher and caps aggression in Europe-linked cyclicals until the conflict premium fades."},{"id":"geo-1","title":"Red Sea shipping corridor remains under intermittent threat","category":"shipping/logistics disruption","region":"Middle East","severity":"High","severityScore":84,"status":"Active","affectedRegions":["Middle East","Europe","Global"],"transmissionChannels":[{"channel":"inflation","direction":"higher","intensity":3,"explanation":"Longer shipping routes keep freight costs and imported goods pressure elevated."},{"channel":"commodities","direction":"higher","intensity":2,"explanation":"Energy and transport-linked commodities keep a risk premium during disruptions."},{"channel":"supplyChain","direction":"mixed","intensity":4,"explanation":"Delivery times and inventory buffers matter more for global manufacturing and retail chains."},{"channel":"riskSentiment","direction":"lower","intensity":2,"explanation":"Headline risk caps aggression in crowded cyclical and consumer names."}],"beneficiaries":["Shipping","Logistics pricing power","Gold","Defense"],"losers":["European cyclicals","Import-dependent retail","Autos"],"actionSuggestion":"add hedge","chips":["freight risk","energy premium","supply chain stress"],"implication":"Keeps freight and energy risk premia elevated; favors resilient quality, select logistics names, and hedge exposure."},{"id":"geo-2","title":"US-China semiconductor restrictions broaden","category":"sanctions","region":"Global","severity":"High","severityScore":80,"status":"Escalation risk","affectedRegions":["United States","China","Asia","Global"],"transmissionChannels":[{"channel":"growth","direction":"lower","intensity":2,"explanation":"Restrictions weigh on capital spending visibility across exposed supply chains."},{"channel":"earnings","direction":"mixed","intensity":4,"explanation":"Leaders with domestic demand hold up better than firms reliant on restricted end markets."},{"channel":"currencies","direction":"mixed","intensity":1,"explanation":"Asia supply-chain currencies remain headline sensitive during policy escalations."},{"channel":"riskSentiment","direction":"lower","intensity":3,"explanation":"AI leaders remain tradable, but sizing discipline matters because headline gaps stay large."}],"beneficiaries":["US localization","Domestic chip tooling","Industrial automation"],"losers":["China-exposed semis","High-beta hardware","Autos with China demand risk"],"actionSuggestion":"monitor","chips":["export controls","AI stack","headline volatility"],"implication":"Creates headline volatility across chips but supports supply-chain localization and domestic capex beneficiaries."},{"id":"geo-5","title":"Tariff rhetoric expands in EV and industrial supply chains","category":"tariffs/trade war","region":"Global","severity":"High","severityScore":78,"status":"Escalating","affectedRegions":["United States","Europe","China"],"transmissionChannels":[{"channel":"growth","direction":"lower","intensity":2,"explanation":"Trade friction slows confidence and pushes businesses toward defensive inventory planning."},{"channel":"earnings","direction":"lower","intensity":3,"explanation":"Margin pressure rises for firms that cannot pass through higher input or tariff costs."},{"channel":"supplyChain","direction":"mixed","intensity":3,"explanation":"Localization beneficiaries can gain share even while cross-border operators lose efficiency."}],"beneficiaries":["Domestic industrials","Localization capex","Infrastructure"],"losers":["EVs","China-exposed autos","Global manufacturers"],"actionSuggestion":"avoid sector","chips":["trade war","margin pressure","localization"],"implication":"Supports localization winners but adds friction to EV, autos, and globally stretched manufacturing chains."},{"id":"geo-4","title":"OPEC+ discipline wobble keeps energy shock risk alive","category":"energy shock","region":"Middle East","severity":"Moderate","severityScore":71,"status":"Monitoring","affectedRegions":["Middle East","Europe","Global"],"transmissionChannels":[{"channel":"inflation","direction":"higher","intensity":3,"explanation":"Oil volatility can re-ignite inflation expectations quickly even if core trends are cooling."},{"channel":"rates","direction":"higher","intensity":2,"explanation":"An energy-led inflation scare would pressure cuts pricing and long-duration multiples."},{"channel":"commodities","direction":"higher","intensity":4,"explanation":"Oil beta and commodity-linked cyclicals remain most sensitive to compliance headlines."}],"beneficiaries":["Energy producers","Commodity exporters","Gold"],"losers":["Airlines","Consumer cyclicals","Rate-sensitive growth"],"actionSuggestion":"avoid sector","chips":["oil beta","inflation risk","policy repricing"],"implication":"Affects oil beta and inflation expectations directly, which can quickly tilt the regime away from duration-sensitive leadership."},{"id":"geo-3","title":"Election volatility rises across major democracies","category":"elections/political instability","region":"United States","severity":"Mod